*** Settings ***
Documentation       Week 0, Week 1 & Week 2 - SM1_STORE2 Schedule Suite
...
...                 **PURPOSE:**
...                 This suite consolidates all BATTC test cases that require Week 0, Week 1, and Week 2 schedule data for Store2.
...                 All tests in this suite use the same week setup, enabling efficient parallel execution.
...
...                 **ONE-TIME SETUP APPROACH:**
...                 Suite Setup executes 'Setup Schedule For Week 0 and 1 wrapped with 'Run Only Once' from pabot.PabotLib.
...                 This ensures schedule setup runs exactly ONCE across all parallel processes before any tests execute.
...
...                 **PARALLEL EXECUTION ENABLED:**
...                 Tests can be executed in parallel using pabot. The setup runs once, then all tests execute concurrently.
...
...                 **TEST CASES INCLUDED:**
...                 Week 0 tests (SM1_STORE2):
...                 - BATTC00139: Verify Week In Progress Schedule Copy Generated By Servlet For Distribution List
...                 - BATTC00143: Verify The Shifts Are Unallocated And Moved To Open Pool After Transfer
...                 - BATTC00144: Verify The Shifts Are Unallocated And Moved To Open Pool After Termination
...                 Week 1 tests (SM1_STORE2):
...                 - BATTC00119: Verify Approval Of Extra Work Shift Response
...                 - BATTC00118: Verify Approval Of Open Shift Response On Web
...                 - BATTC00120: Verify Advertised Shift Response Approval
...                 - BATTC00121: Verify Approval Of Individual Swap Shift Response In Web
...                 - BATTC00186: Verify Approval Of All Eligible Swap Shift Response In Web
...                 - BATTC00193: Verify user is able to do shift trading for new hires
...                 Week 2 tests (SM1_STORE2):
...                 - BATTC00136: Verify User Is Able To Publish Schedule By Running The Servlet For Specific Unit
...                 Weeks 0-2 Navigation (SM1_STORE2):
...                 - BATTC00020: WFM-19-1 Verify Week Navigation For Schedule Page And Review Legends
...                 - BATTC00021: WFM-19-2 Verify Week Navigator On Labor Forecast Page
...                 - BATTC00022: WFM-19-3 Verify Week Navigator On Driver Forecast Page
...
...                 **EXECUTION COMMANDS:**
...
...                 Sequential execution:
...                 uv run python executor.py tests/web/l2_suite/schedule_dependent/week0_week1_week2_sm1store2_schedule_suite.robot --test-env QA28_B0
...
...                 Parallel execution (recommended, 4 processes):
...                 uv run python executor.py tests/web/l2_suite/schedule_dependent/week0_week1_week2_sm1store2_schedule_suite.robot --test-env QA28_B0 --processes 4
...
...                 With browser visible (for debugging):
...                 uv run python executor.py tests/web/l2_suite/schedule_dependent/week0_week1_week2_sm1store2_schedule_suite.robot --test-env QA28_B0 --show-browser
...
...                 **LOCK FILE CLEANUP:**
...                 If setup appears to be skipped, clean pabot lock files before running:
...                 Remove-Item -Path ".pabot_results" -Recurse -Force -ErrorAction SilentlyContinue
...
...                 **ORIGINAL TEST FILES:**
...                 Original individual test files remain in their locations for backward compatibility.
...                 After full validation, they can be deprecated/removed.

