BATTC00119: Verify approval of extra work shift response in web
    [Documentation]
    ...    Tests the complete workflow for extra work shift request, response, and approval.
    ...    Workflow: ESS6_STORE2 raises extra work request → ESS5_STORE2 responds/offers → SM1_STORE2 approves
    ...    Validates: Request creation, response acceptance, notification messages, approval operations
    ...
    ...    Preconditions (Setup via "Setup Schedule For Week template_name=1_0_sm1_store2"):
    ...    - ESS6_STORE2: Has shifts on Day 1, 2, 3. Day 4 is free (available for extra work request).
    ...    - ESS5_STORE2: Has shifts on Day 2, 3. Day 1, 4, 7 are free (can respond to extra work).
    ...    - Schedule is published for current week + 1 (week 1_0)
    ...
    ...    Test Data:
    ...    - Trading Week: Current Week +1 (1_0)
    ...    - Trading Day: Day 4 (1_3)
    ...    - Shift Start Time: 01:00
    ...    - Shift End Time: 23:00
    ...    - Preferred Shift Length: 8:00 Hours
    ...    - Requestor Notes: "Test Additional Work"
    ...
    ...    Test Steps:
    ...    1. ESS6_STORE2 logs in, navigates to shift trade page, raises extra work request for Day 4, logs out
    ...    2. ESS5_STORE2 logs in, navigates to shift trade page, responds to extra work request, logs out
    ...    3. SM1_STORE2 logs in, navigates to schedule page, verifies and approves the response, logs out
    ...    Week: 1, Store: 2
    [Tags]    battc00119    dev:amol    config:weekplan_and_schedule_gen    config:ess_shift_bidding    config:ess
    ...    config:extra_work_shift_enabled    config:auto_approve_extra_work_shift:n    om_hr    checkschedulesetup

    ${extra_work_data}    Get Extra Work Shift Data    planning_week_date=1_0    week_trade_day=1_3
    ...    extra_work_shift_length=9:00    extra_work_request_notes=Test Additional Work
    ...    extra_work_response_notes=Responding to extra work request
    Log    Extra work shift data: ${extra_work_data}

    # Step 1: ESS6_STORE2 raises extra work request for Day 4
    Login And Launch WFM Web App    user_key=ESS6_STORE2
    Navigate To ESS Shift Trade Board Page On Web
    Select Week Number On Shift Trade Board Calendar Page On Web    ${extra_work_data}[planning_week_date]
    Verify Schedule Is Published On Shift Trade Board Page On Web
    Raise Extra Work Request At Day On Shift Trade Board Page On Web    ${extra_work_data}
    ...    ${extra_work_data}[week_trade_day]
    Close Browser

    # Step 2: ESS5_STORE2 responds to/offers for the extra work request
    Login And Launch WFM Web App    user_key=ESS5_STORE2
    Navigate To ESS Shift Trade Board Page On Web
    Select Week Number On Shift Trade Board Calendar Page On Web    ${extra_work_data}[planning_week_date]
    ${requester_user}    Get User    user_key=ESS6_STORE2
    VAR    ${requester_name}    ${requester_user}[displayName]
    Respond To Additional Work Request On Shift Trade Board Page On Web
    ...    ${extra_work_data}[week_trade_day]
    ...    ${requester_name}
    ...    ${extra_work_data}[extra_work_response_notes]
    Close Browser

    # Step 3: SM1_STORE2 verifies and approves the extra work response
    Login And Launch WFM Web App    user_key=SM1_STORE2
    Navigate To RWS Schedule Week Schedule Page On Web
    Select Week Number On Week Schedule Page On Web    ${extra_work_data}[planning_week_date]
    Wait Until Page Is Loaded
    ${is_schedule_published}    Check If Schedule Is In Published State On Web
    Skip If    not ${is_schedule_published}    Schedule is not Published for Current + 1 week - cannot proceed with test.
    ${requester_user}    Get User    user_key=ESS6_STORE2
    VAR    ${requester_name}    ${requester_user}[displayName]
    Approve Extra Work Request Of Associate In SM Week Schedule
    ...    ${requester_name}
    ...    ${extra_work_data}[week_trade_day]

